1<p<\infty
h\in L_p(\mathbb{R})
\left(\displaystyle\int_{\mathbb{R}}|h|^p\right)^{1/p}<\infty
(f_n)_{n\in\mathbb{N}}
f_n(x):=h(x-n)
g\in L_q(\mathbb{R})
\dfrac{1}{p}+\dfrac{1}{q}=1
\lim_{n\to\infty}\displaystyle\int_{\mathbb{R}}f_n g=0
\|f_n\|_p=\|h\|_p<\infty
 |\int_{\mathbb{R}} f_n\cdot g|\le \int_{|x|\le M_1}|f_n\cdot g|+\int_{|x|> M_1}|f_n\cdot g| 
 \int_{\mathbb{R}}f_n\cdot g\to 0
